==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Picric
<hw>Pi"cric</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[Gr. <?/
bitter.]</ety> <fld>(Chem.)</fld> <def>Pertaining to, or designating, a
strong organic acid (called <xex>picric acid</xex>), intensely
bitter.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><note>⟦hand⟧ <xex>Picric acid</xex> is obtained by treating phenol
with strong nitric acid, as a brilliant yellow crystalline substance,
<chform>C6H2(NO2)3.OH</chform>. It is used in dyeing silk and wool, and
also in the manufacture of explosives, as it is very unstable when
heated. Called also <altname>trinitrophenol</altname>, and formerly
<altname>carbazotic acid</altname>.</note>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Picrite</ent>⟦br⟧
